	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Wow, that's interesting ! I however doubt that a whole MMC3 is implemented with so few chips, probably just a subset of it. Considering most MMC3 registers are 6-bit and the 74xx161 is 4-bit, it means two of those would be required for each MMC3 reigster if you wanted to simulate the full chip, something unpractical.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
